# Content Security Policy (CSP) Implementation

## Policy Configuration
The CSP policy is defined in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/server/middleware.ts) with the following directives:

### Resource Loading
- `default-src`: Only allow resources from same origin
- `script-src`: Allow scripts from:
  - Same origin
  - Inline scripts (development)
  - Google Analytics
  - Google Tag Manager
- `style-src`: Allow styles from:
  - Same origin
  - Inline styles
  - Google Fonts
- `img-src`: Allow images from:
  - Same origin
  - Data URLs
  - Contentful CDN
  - Lovable CDN
- `font-src`: Allow fonts from:
  - Same origin
  - Google Fonts

### Security Controls
- `connect-src`: Restrict API connections to:
  - Same origin
  - Contentful API
  - Google Analytics
- `frame-src`: Allow frames only from:
  - Same origin
  - YouTube (for embedded videos)
- `object-src`: Block all object/embed sources
- `base-uri`: Restrict base tag to same origin
- `form-action`: Restrict form submissions to same origin
- `frame-ancestors`: Block site from being framed
- `upgrade-insecure-requests`: Force HTTPS

## Implementation
The policy is:
1. Defined as an object in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/server/middleware.ts)
2. Converted to a string format
3. Applied via security headers middleware
4. Integrated with Vite in [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts)

## Security Headers
Additional security headers are set alongside CSP:
- `X-Content-Type-Options`: Prevent MIME type sniffing
- `X-Frame-Options`: Prevent clickjacking
- `X-XSS-Protection`: Enable XSS filtering
- `Referrer-Policy`: Control referrer information
- `Permissions-Policy`: Restrict browser features
- `Strict-Transport-Security`: Enforce HTTPS
